&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Position Summary&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fleet Operations Lead is responsible for end-to-end operational readiness, compliance, and performance of SHMA’s vehicle fleet. This includes pre-production vehicles, production vehicles, demo vehicles, and internal employee-use vehicles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly cross-functional, execution-focused leadership role. You will ensure that every vehicle in the fleet is safe, digitally enabled, insured, licensed, compliant, and operational across testing, storage, transportation, demonstrations, and employee use.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner closely with Engineering, IT, Customer Service, Quality, Legal, Finance, People Operations, and Retail/Studio Operations to build scalable, compliant, and efficient fleet processes as SHMA moves toward commercialization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone who thrives in fast-paced environments, enjoys building structure where none exists, and takes pride in operational ownership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fleet Maintenance &amp;amp; Vehicle Readiness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own fleet maintenance strategy across pre-production, production, demo, and employee-use vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee preventive maintenance, repairs, inspections, and vendor coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering and IT to manage OTA software updates to ensure vehicles remain current, secure, and operational&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track maintenance schedules, issue resolution, and downtime metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure vehicles are fully operational and presentation-ready for demos, testing, internal use, and events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal Employee Fleet Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end operations for SHMA’s internal employee vehicle fleet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and enforce fleet usage policies, including eligibility, access controls, safety standards, and acceptable use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate employee onboarding and offboarding for fleet participation, including assignment, provisioning, and vehicle return&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with People Operations, Legal, and Finance to ensure compliance with labor, insurance, and risk policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor utilization, costs, and vehicle condition to optimize program performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Payments, Accounts &amp;amp; Digital Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage fleet-related accounts and subscriptions including insurance, charging services, and connected vehicle applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee digital services subscriptions and integrations for fleet vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance to manage renewals, budgeting, invoice tracking, and cost controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate documentation and cost transparency across fleet operations&lt;/li&gt

